dez, and then shot Mendez once in the head. Mendez later died of his injuries. Cosgaya-Alvarez was arrested a few days later in [[Seattle]] and was charged with murder.<ref name=\"komonews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.komonews.com/news/local/27107034.html|title=Teen sought in school shooting captured, charged|publisher=[[KOMO News]]|date=August 18, 2008|accessdate=January 28, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140827152532/http://www.komonews.com/news/local/27107034.html|archivedate=August 27, 2014}}</ref> Cosgaya-Alvarez pleaded guilty to murder and weapon enhancements and was sentenced to 18 years in prison.<ref name=\"courtswa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.courts.wa.gov/opinions/index.cfm?fa=opinions.showOpinion&filename=669788MAJ|title=State Of Washington, Res. V. Luis Cosgaya-alvarez|publisher=State of Washington|date=January 14, 2013|accessdate=January 28, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 19, 2008\n| [[Krugersdorp, Gauteng|Krugersdorp]],<br>[[Gauteng]],<br>South Africa\n| Morn\u00e9 Harmse, 18\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| [[Nic Diederichs Technical High School slashing]]. One student was killed and another student and two campus [[groundskeeper]]s were wounded at Nic Diederichs Technical High School, in [[Krugersdorp]], South Africa, after 18-year-old [[Matriculation in South Africa|matrics]] student Morn\u00e9 Harmse had slashed them with a [[samurai sword]]. On October 10, 2009 Harmse was sentenced to 20 years in jail.<ref name=\"NEWS242\">{{cite web|title = 'Want to see something cool?'|author1 = du Plessis, Lean\u00e9|author2 = Amanda Roestoff|publisher= [[News24]]|date = August 18, 2008|url = http://www.news24.com/News24/South_Africa/News/0,,2-7-1442_2378386,00.html|accessdate = 2008-09-17|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080917224158/http://www.news24.com/News24/South_Africa/News/0,,2-7-1442_2378386,00.html|archive-date = 2008-09-17|url-status = dead}}</ref><ref name=\"NEWS241\">{{cite web|title = Harmse 'liked to sharpen sword'