ore]],<br>[[Saint Catherine Parish|St. Catherine]],<br>[[Jamaica]]\n| ..., 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| The [[Dean (academics)|Dean of Discipline]] of [[Ascot High School]], in [[Portmore, Jamaica|Portmore]], [[Jamaica]], was stabbed in the neck while inside his office by a 15-year-old student at the school. The dean was treated at a local hospital and released.<ref name=\"jamaicastardean\">{{cite news|title=Dean of discipline stabbed|date=2009-04-30|url=http://www.jamaica-star.com/thestar/20090430/news/news13.html|work=The Jamaica Star|accessdate=2009-05-28|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090503155302/http://www.jamaica-star.com/thestar/20090430/news/news13.html|archivedate=2009-05-03}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 5, 2009\n| [[Canandaigua]],<br>[[New York (state)|New York]],<br>United States\n| Thomas Kane, 17\n| 1 dead\n| \n| A 17-year-old senior shot and killed himself in a bathroom at [[Canandaigua Academy]] in [[Canandaigua, New York]]. He had 30 rounds of ammunition and two explosive devices in his locker. Police said Thomas Kane used a sawed-off shotgun and died of a self-inflicted gunshot wound but did not use the Molotov cocktail-type devices, two glass bottles filled with liquid and rags, that were in his locker. The school was put on lockdown following the morning shooting and students were evacuated and taken to Canandaigua Middle School. No one else was hurt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whec.com/news/stories/S918633.shtml?cat=565|title=Page Not Found|website=whec.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 11, 2009\n| [[Sankt Augustin]],<br>[[North Rhine-Westphalia]],<br>Germany\n| Tanja Otto, 16\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old student, Tanja Otto, entered the Albert Einstein [[Gymnasium (school)|gymnasium]] (high school), in [[Sankt Augustin]], Germany, carrying knives, [[incendiary bombs|incendiary explosives]], [[gunpowder]], a [[flamethrower]], and an [[air gun|air-powered pistol]]. Otto attempted to [[arson|torch]] the school but was confronted by another stu