 Says He Was Bullied|publisher=[[Associated Press]] |date=January 11, 2012 |accessdate=September 9, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 13, 2012\n|[[Xuzhou]], [[Jiangsu]], China\n| Haoyu Feng\n| 1 dead\n| \n| [[Xuzhou No.32 Middle School homicide]]. 15-year-old Xiangyu Wang was stabbed and killed by a fellow student at Xuzhou No.32 Middle School, with who he had disputed with in the past. Feng had threaten to kill Wang with his new dagger the day before the attack, after the two were in an online argument in a chatroom. The victim bleed to death due to the lack of emergency treatment. He was pronounced dead at the hospital the same day as the attack, at 2:50 p.m. The school was accused of failing to save the victim. No school teachers, faculties, or staffs tried to perform first-aid on Wang, and neither did they call emergency services, despite knowing about the incident. Wang was transported to hospital with help of his classmates. The on-campus doctor resumed teaching her art class, knowing Wang was bleeding heavily. The school administration refused to accept any media nor did they apologise for the incident.\n|-\n| February 27, 2012\n|[[Chardon, Ohio|Chardon]],<br>[[Ohio]],<br>United States\n| T.J. Lane, 17\n| 3 dead\n| 3 injured\n|[[Chardon High School shooting]]. Six students were shot at Chardon High School. One student, Daniel Parmentor, died at the scene, and on February 28, two other students, Russell King and Demetrius Hewlin, also died. One of the three others wounded was in critical condition. The shooter, Thomas \"T.J.\" Lane, was taken into police custody. Lane was reported to have had a \"rivalry\" with King, although was unfamiliar with any other victims. In March 2013, Lane was convicted of the crimes and was sentenced to life in prison without parole.\n|-\n| March 1, 2012\n| [[Sulaimaniyah]], [[Kurdistan]], [[Iraq]]\n| Biyar Sarwar, 18\n| 2 dead\n| \n| 18-year-old Biyar Sarwar shot American gym teacher Jeremiah Small three times in the head and chest at 