ring High School|url=http://abclocal.go.com/ktrk/story?section=news/local&id=9235459|publisher=KTRK TV|accessdate=5 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906070232/http://abclocal.go.com/ktrk/story?section=news%2Flocal&id=9235459|archive-date=6 September 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n|{{Dts|September 20, 2013}}\n|[[Vereeniging]], [[South Africa]] \n| Student\n|\n| 1 injured \n|A Grade 9 student shot a teacher in the leg at Sasolburg High School. The student was arrested.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pupil shoots teacher at Vereeniging school\n|url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Pupil-shoots-teacher-at-Vereeniging-school-20130920|publisher=[[News24]]|date=20 September 2012|accessdate=6 October 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|September 24, 2013}}\n|[[Greeneville, Tennessee]], United States\n| Jacob Mitchell, 17\n|\n| 1 injured \n|A 15-year-old student was stabbed and injured at [[South Greene High School]] before classes started. Students subdued the assailant until staff members arrived on scene. The victim was hospitalized in stable condition. The suspect, a student, was charged with attempted first-degree murder. The suspect, Jacob Mitchell, is being tried as an adult for attempted murder. Mitchell faces up to 15 to 25 years of prison if convicted.<ref>{{cite web|title=Student charged with attempted first degree murder after stabbing at South Greene H.S.|url=http://www.wjhl.com/story/23512929/2013/09/24/breaking-stabbing-at-south-greene-high-school|publisher=[[WJHL]]|date=September 24, 2013|accessdate=October 7, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227051910/http://www.wjhl.com/story/23512929/2013/09/24/breaking-stabbing-at-south-greene-high-school|archivedate=February 27, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Student stabbed at Tennessee high school|url=http://www.timesfreepress.com/news/2013/sep/25/student-stabbed-tennessee-high-school/|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|date=September 25, 2013|accessdate=October 7, 2013