of the [[Taiwan|Republic of China (Taiwan)]]</center>\nImage:Flag of Tibet.svg|<center>[[Flag of Tibet]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n;wavy rays ([[estoile]])\n<gallery>\nImage:G\u00f6teborg stift vapen.svg|<center>Arms of the [[Diocese of Gothenburg]]</center>\nImage:Escut Jekabpils rajonas.jpg|<center>Arms of [[J\u0113kabpils District]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Kazakhstan.svg|<center>[[Flag of Kazakhstan]]</center>\nImage:Flag of Kyrgyzstan.svg|<center>[[Flag of Kyrgyzstan]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n;without rays ([[roundel]])\n<gallery>\nFile:Australian Aboriginal Flag.svg|<center>[[Australian Aboriginal Flag]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Japan.svg|<center>[[Flag of Japan]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Bangladesh.svg|<center>[[Flag of Bangladesh]]</center>\n</gallery>\n;other forms\n<gallery>\n\nFile:Naval Ensign of Japan.svg|<center>[[Naval Ensign]] of Japan</center>\nImage:Coat of Arms of Latvia.svg|<center>[[Coat of arms of Latvia]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Macedonia.svg|<center>[[Flag of the Republic of Macedonia]]</center>\n\nFile:Flag_of_Philippines.svg|<center>Flag of the Philippines</center>\nFile:Naval Jack of the Philippines.svg|<center>[[Naval Jack of the Philippines]]</center>\nImage:Seal of the First Philippine Republic.svg|<center>Emblem of the [[First Philippine Republic|Philippines]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n{{Commons category|Sun in heraldry}}\n*[[Solar symbol]]\n*[[Splendor Solis]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n\n[[Category:Heraldic charges]]\n[[Category:Sun]]\n\n[[fr:Liste des meubles h\u00e9raldiques#Soleil]]\n", "text_old": "[[Image:H\u00e9raldique meuble Soleil avec visage.svg|thumb|The sun as a [[Charge (heraldry)|charge]]]]\n[[File:Sol de Mayo-Bandera de Argentina.svg|thumb| [[Sun of May]] as depicted on the flag of [[Argentina]]]]\n[[File:Risa3.jpg|thumb|Great Seal of [[Richard I of England]] (1198). Richard is depicted as seated between a [[crescent]] and a \"Sun full radiant\"<ref>English heraldic tradition of the early modern period associates the [[star and crescent]] design with Richard, with his victory over [[Isaac Komnenos of Cyprus]] in 1192, and with the arms of [[Portsmouth]] (Francis Wise ''A Letter to Dr Mead Concerning Some Antiquities in Berkshire'', 1738, [https://books.google.com/books?id=cFAGAAAAQAAJ&pg=RA1-PA18 p. 18]). Heraldic tradition also attributes a star-and-crescent [[:File:Complete Guide to Heraldry Fig680.png|badge]] to Richard (Charles Fox-Davies, ''A Complete Guide to Heraldry'', 1909, p. 468).</ref>]]\n\nA representation of the '''[[sun]]''' is used as a [[heraldry|heraldic]] [[Charge (heraldry)|charge]].  The most usual form, often called '''sun in splendour''' or '''in his glory''', consists of a round disc with the features of a human face surrounded by twelve or sixteen rays alternating wavy and straight.<ref>[http://www.heraldsnet.org/saitou/parker/Jpglosss.htm#Sun James Parker, ''A glossary of terms used in heraldry''].  Accessed 13 December 2009</ref><ref name=\"vexillology\">[http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/Flags/vxt-dvs6.html#suninspendour Dictionary of Vexillology].  Accessed 13 December 2009</ref>  The alternating straight and wavy rays are often said to represent the light and heat of the sun respectively.<ref>Fox-Davies, A.C., (1969) ''A complete guide to heraldry.'' Aylesbury: Thomas Nelson and Sons. p. 222.</ref>\n\nIt was used as a badge by [[Edward II of England]], and was later adopted by [[Edward IV]] following the appearance of a [[parhelion]] or \"sun dog\" before his victory at the [[Battle of Mortimer's Cross]] in 1461.<ref name=\"vexillology\"/><ref>[http://www.britannica.com/bps/additionalcontent/18/7057128/Edward-IV-and-the-Alchemists Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica: Edward IV and the Alchemists]. Accessed 13 December 2009</ref>\nIt also had significance in [[alchemy]], and may be a symbol of the [[Roman mythology|Roman deity]] ''[[Sol Invictus]]'' (Unconquered Sun).<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010630033912/http://www.kickback.btinternet.co.uk/History.and.Archaeology/Banbury/Faith/Trail.html Banbury Faith Trail].  Accessed 13 December 2009</ref>\n\nIt is a common charge in the heraldry of many countries; ''e.g.'' the bearings of [http://archive.gg.ca/heraldry/pub-reg/project.asp?lang=e&ProjectID=1030 Armstrong], Canada, and the arms of [http://www.civicheraldry.co.uk/thames_valley_chilterns.html#banbury%20tc Banbury Town Council], England.\nIt also often appears as a rising sun as in the arms of [http://www.civicheraldry.co.uk/cornwall_wessex.html#east%20devon%20dc East Devon District Council], England, and as a demi sun as in the coat of [http://archive.gg.ca/heraldry/pub-reg/project.asp?lang=e&ProjectID=114&ShowAll=1 Aitchison], Canada.\n\nThe [[Sun of May]] shown on the [[national flag]]s of [[flag of Argentina|Argentina]] (1818)  and [[flag of Uruguay|Uruguay]] (1828) is identical in form to the \"Sun in Splendour\".\n\n==Examples==\n{{Refimprove section|date=January 2009}}\n;Sun in splendour, with face\n<gallery>\nImage:Blason famille fr Amelot.svg|<center>Arms of Amelot family</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Argentina.svg|<center>[[Flag of Argentina]]</center>\nImage:Blason Arraincourt 57.svg|<center>Arms of [[Arraincourt]]</center>\nImage:Blason ville fr Auzeville-Tolosane (Haute-Garonne).svg|<center>Arms of [[Auzeville-Tolosane]]</center>\nImage:Basse terre blason.png|<center>Arms of [[Basse-Terre]]</center>\nImage:Blason ville-fr Bassurels (Loz\u00e8re).svg|<center>Arms of [[Bassurels]]</center>\nImage:Blason Creisset.svg|<center>Arms of [[Beynes, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence|Creisset]]</center>\nImage:CUB-cuba.png|<center>Arms of [[Cuba Municipality|Cuba]] (Portugal)</center>\nImage:Blason ville fr Dole (Jura).svg|<center>Arms of [[Dole (Jura)]]</center>\nImage:Escudo de Ecija.png|<center>Arms of [[\u00c9cija]]</center>\nImage:Ennetburgen-coat of arms.svg|<center>Arms of [[Ennetb\u00fcrgen]]</center>\nImage:Blason ville fr Fontaines-Saint-Martin (Rh\u00f4ne).svg|<center>Arms of [[Fontaines-Saint-Martin]]</center>\nImage:Wappen Kaenerkinden.png|<center>Arms of [[K\u00e4nerkinden]]</center>\nImage:Kampod_r.gif|<center>Arms of [[Kamianets-Podilsky]]</center>\nImage:Coat_of_Arms_of_Khmelnytskyi_Oblast.svg|<center>Arms of [[Khmelnytskyi Oblast]]</center>\nImage:Loukov znak.png|<center>Arms of [[Loukov (Krom\u011b\u0159\u00ed\u017e District)|Loukov]]</center>\nImage:Blason Mende.png|<center>Arms of [[Mende, Loz\u00e8re|Mende]]</center>\nFile:Flag of Peru (1822).svg|<center>[[Flag of Peru#Flag of March 1822|1822 Flag of Peru]]</center>\nFile:Philippines flag original.png|<center>[[Flag of the Philippines]] (1899-1901)</center>\nImage:Wappen at st gilgen.png|<center>Arms of [[Sankt Gilgen]]</center>\nImage:Escut del Soler\u00e0s.svg|<center>Arms of [[:es:El Soler\u00e0s|El Soler\u00e0s]]</center>\nFile:Napeshold.jpg|<center>Historical flag of [[Sz\u00e9kely Land]]</center>\nImage:POL wojew\u00f3dztwo tarnopolskie II RP COA.svg|<center>Arms of [[Tarnopol Voivodeship]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Uruguay.svg|<center>[[Flag of Uruguay]]</center>\nImage:Vedomice znak.jpg|<center>Arms of [[V\u011bdomice]]</center>\nImage:V\u011b\u017eky PR znak.png|<center>Arms of [[V\u011b\u017eky (P\u0159erov District)|V\u011b\u017eky]]</center>\nImage:Coat_of_Arms_of_Vinnytsa_Oblast.svg|<center>Arms of [[Vinnytsia Oblast]]</center>\nImage:Coat_of_Arms_of_Zhytomyr_Oblast.svg|<center>Arms of [[Zhytomyr Oblast]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n;Sun in splendour, without face\n<gallery>\nImage:Escudo de Archena.svg|<center>Arms of [[Archena]]</center>\nImage:CH Arosa COA.svg|<center>Arms of [[Arosa]]</center>\nImage:Blason ville fr Barb\u00e2tre (Vend\u00e9e).svg|<center>Arms of [[Barb\u00e2tre]]</center>\nImage:Blason ville fr La Baule-Escoublac (Loire-Atlantique).svg|<center>Arms of [[La Baule-Escoublac]]</center>\nFile:Flag of Colorado Party (Uruguay).svg|<center>Flag of the Colorado Party, in the [[Uruguayan Civil War]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n;straight rays ([[mullet (heraldry)|mullet]])\n<gallery>\nImage:Escudo de Beri\u00e1in.svg|<center>Arms of [[Beri\u00e1in]]</center>\nImage:DEU Dobel COA.svg|<center>Arms of [[Dobel]]</center>\nImage:Escudo de Galar.svg|<center>Arms of [[Galar]]</center>\nImage:Flag of Greek Macedonia.svg|<center>[[Flag of Macedonia (Greece)]] ([[Vergina Sun]])</center>\nFile:Flag of Szekely Land.svg|<center>Current flag of [[Sz\u00e9kely Land]]</center>\nFile:Flag_of_the_Republic_of_China.svg|<center>Flag of the [[Taiwan|Republic of China (Taiwan)]]</center>\nImage:Flag of Tibet.svg|<center>[[Flag of Tibet]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n;wavy rays ([[estoile]])\n<gallery>\nImage:G\u00f6teborg stift vapen.svg|<center>Arms of the [[Diocese of Gothenburg]]</center>\nImage:Escut Jekabpils rajonas.jpg|<center>Arms of [[J\u0113kabpils District]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Kazakhstan.svg|<center>[[Flag of Kazakhstan]]</center>\nImage:Flag of Kyrgyzstan.svg|<center>[[Flag of Kyrgyzstan]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n;without rays ([[roundel]])\n<gallery>\nFile:Australian Aboriginal Flag.svg|<center>[[Australian Aboriginal Flag]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Japan.svg|<center>[[Flag of Japan]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Bangladesh.svg|<center>[[Flag of Bangladesh]]</center>\n</gallery>\n;other forms\n<gallery>\n\nFile:Naval Ensign of Japan.svg|<center>[[Naval Ensign]] of Japan</center>\nImage:Coat of Arms of Latvia.svg|<center>[[Coat of arms of Latvia]]</center>\nImage:Flag_of_Macedonia.svg|<center>[[Flag of the Republic of Macedonia]]</center>\n\nFile:Flag_of_Philippines.svg|<center>Flag of the Philippines</center>\nFile:Naval Jack of the Philippines.svg|<center>[[Naval Jack of the Philippines]]</center>\nImage:Seal of the First Philippine Republic.svg|<center>Emblem of the [[First Philippine Republic|Philippines]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n{{Commons category|Sun in heraldry}}\n*[[Solar symbol]]\n*[[Splendor Solis]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n\n[[Category:Heraldic charges]]\n[[Category: